                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1143">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Sherman</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Loomis</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-04-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 21, 1898</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Ultimatum served yesterday through Spanish minister here and by instruction to
                    United States minister, Madrid. Spanish Government broke off diplomatic
                    relations before latter could communicate. This Government is now free to act as
                    though refused. War appears inevitable. You will be at once advised.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sherman.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
